[SN]TITLE[SN]
Driver killed in Blaenavon car and lorry crash named

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man who died after the car he was driving was involved in a crash with a lorry in Torfaen has been named by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Adam Phillip Michael Millett, 26, was driving a silver Renault Megane which collided with a flatbed lorry in Garn Y Erw, near Blaenavon on Friday.
The driver of the lorry received minor injuries.
Gwent Police says Mr Millett's family is being supported by specialist officers.
